Elven Princess Mage.FIELD7: This card is actually flower fencer with a -1/1. Even that is incredible. You have flexibility in holding them for combo or swarming board. One of the insta picks alongside anything playable.

Fairy Princess.FIELD7: You almost always take this with another playable. Stats aren't great but this thing draws you 5-7 cards late game and enables all your combos.

Ancient Forest Dragon.FIELD7: Great defensive body and ability and helps protect you and the team. Kind of like a dragonewt charlotte pick when your sword. Sometimes you might want to curve lower but in general this is amazing to draw late.

Sylvan justice.FIELD7: 2 damage is enough early to kill problematic stuff stalling ur board. Gives you some card advantage and combo fodder later.

Robin Hood.FIELD7: Gimmicky ability vs removal keeping x/1's alive which usually messes u up with 1 evo charge. But good stats post evo. Fairies rare pool isn't as solid and this one is one of the best.

Crystalia Tia.FIELD7: Does things when it comes out, can be saved for combo or put as a simple 1/1 + 4/4 with evolve flexability. Solid like noble knight when non comboing much better when ofc but your 5's tend to come out on curve. No combo's with Elven Priestess like contructed.

Elf Knight Cynthia.FIELD7: Fills out one thing forest struggles to have which is a premium fatty. A lot of their 5/6's are understated with unreliable/useful effects this one puts bodies on board and trades up into other lategame drops without dying.

Yuel the Ancient.FIELD7: This card is forests 2 for 1 that they never got on 4. Elven is still insane but this with lots of low drop fairies can blow out opponents trying to trade up on your weenies (one of the common problems was ur 1/x's died to x/2's and x/3's and u had only evolve crashes or draft removal to interact with board). This probably stays in arena rotation since it's new even though it's good, (Guessing FF, D warrior and such are getting cut from arena).

Waltzing Fairy.FIELD7: Generates a ton of value by itself almost guarenteed at the cost of some statpoints. Arena isn't as demanding on ur statline early as long you have stuff to play on curve and fairy tends to do that fine.

Elf Tracker.FIELD7: Really good card for what your doing and how the opponent trades. You can set up great clears with her pings and she evo trades into something midsized effectively. Unless your going super early game and even then you still want these in ur deck.

Forest Archelon.FIELD7: Insane effect to get off lategame when you play this and dictate trades later and solid fatty stats that forest tend to lack.

Verdant Steward.FIELD7: Quite a nice card with good statline to trade and it gives you your combo fodder lategame or just free value and protects you and your weenies. Forest didn't have a consistant high attack/toughness go to common at 5 until this I believe.

Elf Girl Liza.FIELD7: Solid pick, you play her as a 2/2 with upside as filler with another good card. She gives forest another good rare card that blanks removal for a turn making ur traded in 4/1's and such imposible to remove with conventional removal tools.

Fairy Circle.FIELD7: Turn 1 generally is passed and this gives you oathless knight on 2 or you can stockpile fairies for later. Late game it enables a combo on a single card.

Fairy Whisperer.FIELD7: A tad weak on the frontside but generates cards from nothing letting you win a value game and save for combos later. Really good with a triple drop followup on T3/4

Elf Guard.FIELD7: Amazing statline especially for this craft which is going to be losing it's 1/x's a lot to 1/2s and 2/2's to keep you on par with board. Combo effect is extra icying on top when it's enabled.

Ancient Elf.FIELD7: Giving this a solid thumbs up since she has a good statline saves people from dying and puts a huge body on board early to contest board. Again can mess u up but you can set it up to be beneficial with trades and fanfare bounces.

Elf Prophetess.FIELD7: Great stats and ward with the bounce is generally controlable or neglected on an empty board.

Noble Fairy.FIELD7: Great ability but your fairies aren't quickbladers so you need pings or an established board of low drops to really benefit alongside combo in hand. ainly a 4/4 with some great text that works sometimes.

Will of the Forest.FIELD7: This often acts as a decently spellboosted fire chain for most fairy decks midgame with trades from a decent board you should be able to clear with it.

Forest Giant.FIELD7: The 4 cost spell on a body that finishes off something weakened or a low drop and puts a respectable body on board. Things like this alongside other big drops help bridge your generally pitaful lategame.

Grand Archer Selwyn.FIELD7: More good stuff at rare. You pick him as a 6 cause you need a 6 and he helps you push a developing board with his 'stun' when opponents start putting out big midrange stuff. Lets you dictate trades or go for final push. Unevolve easyish bounce condition for free is really good too.

Elf Bard.FIELD7: Every Craft gets a cycle of these cards, I'll rate this on highly cause it replaces itself on midgame 'for free' and acts like a sylvan justice attack on a 2/2 which is fine. You need to draft your vanilla 2's anyway.

Elf Metallurgist.FIELD7: More reliable later in the game in a way and below par dropping it on 2. Gets better as you draft more fairy generators. Quite a bit of blowout potential.

Elf Child May.FIELD7: Crazy good when trading early with your 1/x's and helpes your combos midgame. Ping is reliable most of the time to get rid of problem followers on low health.

Fairy Bringer.FIELD7: I value this statline a lot especially in this craft. Effect is good for combo and swarming early. You don't want too many of high health low drops though but an alluring pick if it's in your first couple picks.

Dark Elf Faure.FIELD7: 2/3 is good stats for trading. Hitting once with it is amazing value and it's fairycrafts only common 2/3 to draft.

Pixie Paradise.FIELD7: It does nothing at first but sets you up later. It's good where you have those turns you don't want to put more out or have free mana open. Win condition on it's own but needs survival support.

Rose Gardener.FIELD7: Either insanely OP of underwhelming depending on your situation. Solid pick that can win the game on it's own with a bounce trade but less good in long games.

Baalt, King of the Elves.FIELD7: Not a bad card per se but not as much of a high pick compared to early game premiums. You'll still be very happy to take this as one of your top ends for sure. Does a decent Noble knight + impression and evolves into a 7 hp butt.

Rhinoroach.FIELD7: You can make people scared by the sound it makes with it's fanfare I guess. Usually just a removal spell scaling with combo and less likely to be potent than in constructed but a decent enough 2 mana damage spell.

Elemental Lance.FIELD7: Removal is removal, 3 for 3 is a fair rate and the combo mid to late game comes up enough.

Fairy Caster.FIELD7: You trade stats for combo fodder and late game you get a free board. Other than the stat downside which hurst a lot if this is one of ur fatty slots it's a good pick with enough combo synergies.

Magna Botanist.FIELD7: Fairies sage commander that's a bit hard to proc but is crazy when it does. You'll pick it as a 6 if you need it but quite hard to pull it off and be winning at the same time without and insane deck.

Elder Treant.FIELD7: Nice ability if it triggers and average without it. Another 6 drop that you take just cause u want one.

Water Fairy.FIELD7: Often better than a 1/2 sometimes worse, relies quite a bit on your early game sward and fairy generation but you tend to be wanting to draft that kind of deck.

Blessed Fairy Dancer.FIELD7: Winmorish but helps solidify your board with trades and pushes damage. Great that it's non combo too so you can use it to some potency late game. Gets more enticing the lower the drop of a deck you can make.

Archer.FIELD7: Similar problems it runs into in constructed where you need a clear board to play it or combo it later but both those aren't guarenteed in arena but still has uses as a midgame ping, evo clear or snowballing a board.

Fen Sprite.FIELD7: Great in a low curve deck and annoying for those without a lot of damage spells and pings. Helps protect your fairys from efficient trades to let you dictage them for a turn. Statline is horrid though and quite specific deck type needs to be drafted.

Tam Lin.FIELD7: it's good as a 3/3 but sometimes will be awkward to find the best spot to card alongside a fairy. Dropping it as your 3 will happen quite often without enough generators I feel.

Okami.FIELD7: No longer as nice pick with forest having 3 premium 4 drops.

Dwarf Perfumer.FIELD7: Has a really odd statline in forest but a pretty easy to trigger ability that is annoying and pretty strong. Lets you push or trade flexibly and can come down to threaten with it's high power. Less good the more midrange ur curve is. More better with your early drops + fairy generators to protect.

Dungeoncrawl Fairy.FIELD7: Actually doesn't bounce itself so you can drop it on 2 for an early drop. reuses fanfares later, heals stuff by replaying and generates a combo with it and a combo card. Nice curve fuller. Messes u up sometimes though.

Elf Wanderer.FIELD7: Usually useless ability but a 2 drop for fairy that can hit stuff early. Draft it when you need your 2's.

Glimmering Wings.FIELD7: Has a lot of potential drafting more low curving stuff but will be more like filler similar to conscription. Your deck quality has to be pretty premium to want to have a 29 card deck.

Pixie Mischief.FIELD7: Only if you have a constructed level early game and even then it is barely crazy. You struggle to push board and tempo bounce reuse fanfare isn't as potent in arena in non dream situations.

Homecoming.FIELD7: It's playable in a sense but so many situations where this just skips a turn for both sides and you end up in the same situation.

Rose Queen.FIELD7: The potential is there and you don't need too many to get value but ur craft tends to have to use fairies for other combos and to stay on board.

Fairy Champion.FIELD7: Usually just something to annoy people with and dies for free to a lot of things. But you can trade a card for tempo and it has it's place in a low curving aggro fairy deck.

Nature's Guidance.FIELD7: Anti tempo for reusing a fanfare and draw. Relies on too many synergies to get off reliably but helps with combos later in the game.

Wandering Elf Mage.FIELD7: You don't want to be drafting all low drops all the time and in a standard curving out deck this is just a 2/1 for 2 which gets picked off by pings, tokens and 1 drops. Solid combo draw late though but not too exciting.

Woodkin Curse.FIELD7: A bit more pickable than I rate it but similar to the shadowcraft bane spell. Gets better with your fairy generators and an ok slot to have as your removal pieces.

Forest of Dreams.FIELD7: Random is a buzzkill and doesnt help you on board since stalling doesn't help as much. The follower version of this with a fanfare is much better.

Mana Elk.FIELD7: Does some cute things and makes most of your followers hit hard but doesn't help with board and has a slightly worse statline than other 4's.

Petal Fencer.FIELD7: Obviously this is better with more generators but you don't have unlimited copies of them so your stream of 2/2's isn't as scary. Still a great thing to pull off midgame with 2/3 fairies but this is more of a pick alongside a solid rare/legend.

Way of the Outlaw.FIELD7: Tends to be overcosted removal early and deadish late but can fill in a removal slot as a damage filler.

Harvest Festival.FIELD7: Yah. Harvest festival did nothing wrong. Except it did. So we have this now which is still ok but not where your average mana cost is much higher and you don't have much combo steam to begin with.

Treant.FIELD7: Grows pretty big later and meh stats to start. But 5 drop evos to kill other stuff are important to have so a fair inclusion.

Fairy Beast.FIELD7: Again you'll take if you need one but the heal tends to be unneeded/inconsistant and the stats are underwhelming.

Elven Archery.FIELD7: Pretty bad since it's like Roach but worse, you have to have a healthy hand to dump midgame(which you should be dumping early) and want to play this for at least like 3 to get decent value and even then it's just averagish removal. Comboey removal though.

Master of the Canopies.FIELD7: Not that godly unfortuantely. 1/1 scaling that requires you to have a hand where your general game plan is dumping stuff to seize board. Just averageish at a +4/+4 or +5/+5 which is pretty common to have around that size.

Underbrush Beast Girl.FIELD7: Sadly not an ambush most of the time making it a desert rider but has some ninja master impressions midgame for the delayed 4 damage anywhere. Still bad in that it's a combo requirement and dropping it as a vanilla isn't winning you any games.

Elf Healer.FIELD7: Statline is quite bad doesn't trade as much but has the upside in being in a craft that generates 1/1's out of nothing to kinda trade into x/2's. Still weakish and unreliable. Heal is basically blank text most of the time even if it saves you in a game. You'll take this as a 3 drop filler with something good.

Carnivorous Flower.FIELD7: Dies to a lot and is mana too much. Still pickable with another playable in that pile as a damage based 3 drop with some at times relavent combo ability.

Titatnia's Santuary.FIELD7: You need to have enough fairy generators, draw this do nothing card just to give +2/+2 storm to a fairy. Tons of investment and the dream isn't enough to justify.

Woodland Refuge.FIELD7: The advantage you get from being a card down isn't enough even if you were to draft a really low curving deck it still wouldn't put you ahead.

Entangling Vines.FIELD7: Flexibility pushes this higher than other removals

Swords to Woodlands.FIELD7: I want to say it's a bit better than elemental lance

Felpurr Kitten.FIELD7: Not as good as may, but better than water fairy

Forest Spirit.FIELD7: woodkin is not a great card but it is card advantage

Forest Gigas.FIELD7: Ward on 7 is good, but you may not have enough cards by then

Dark Angel Olivia.FIELD7: She lets you play in an unconventional way which lets you dominate board by wasting your evos. You obviously do this with her in hand if you employ that strategy. With 2 more evo charges assumking you rush her as a 6/6 you should be able to outvalue the opponent if still around even. Late gamey like satan with the lower impact if games out of reach.

Lucifer.FIELD7: Games can be won off of him both agressively and defensively. Helps completely stablize and also provides a threat. Awkward when you need to evolve him to trade though. But better than a lot of craft legends.

Gabriel.FIELD7: Awkward to land in practice and sometimes tend to be winmorish but makes a trade out of nowhere and has solid added statlines. Usually icing alongside another good gold or double legend pick.

Odin.FIELD7: Just a banish ability on legs. Solid lategame card with your pile. More towards filler in board reliant early game crafts similar to satan/lucifer but should be nice in those that want to go late or play value game.

Surefire Bullet.FIELD7: Kills basically everything evolved that ran into something and a neutral soul hunt without the condition which is a solid removal. I expect this to be quite common from all crafts as a high quality pick.

Athena.FIELD7: Make board, trade in, Blow out. less good in more spell/amulet decks ofc but in any deck that want's to be trading for board since it drops early it's quite nice.

Gilgamesh.FIELD7: Finisher quality pick for any swarmy deck that wants a late drop that doesn't just die for free. Great for trading as a removal spell or ramming into 2/x's for profit leaving a threatening body.

Humpty Dumty.FIELD7: Great for the crafts that want it. Think of it as a super dragon warrior that kills everything around it and itself. Or just a Lore on a stick. Terrible as a vanilla and aggro/board centric drafts though.

Dance Of Death.FIELD7: Crimson purge +1 deals damage to enemy face. Just an excecution with upside most of the time which is quite good.

Healing Angel.FIELD7: Trades incredibly well with it's 2/3 statline and has a relavent body of text. One of the premium common's to be bundled with your picks.

Spellbook Decryption.FIELD7: Again another later game refill card that wins topdeck wars in neutral games. Pretty bad rate but you will take alongside something good.

Execution.FIELD7: Removal is quite nice and not too much weaker than craft specific ones. You'll want a couple damage/hard removal tools against big fatties that most crafts get access too from their gold/legend picks.

Goblinmount Demon.FIELD7: Similar to constructed where you want to play tis in a controlling deck as it's kinda awkward in a board control follower based deck which you tend to draft. Still premium stats are nice and can usually make up for trading your board in to something moderate while estabilishing this.

Harnessed Glass.FIELD7: Actually passable when evolving and hits like a 4/4 with aoe very similar to a necroelementalist for neutral when it works. Usually u can guage it and save it for surprise aoe or just drop it on a decent board and have it soak removal or it can skew tons of trades.

Demonic Strike.FIELD7: Neutral Removal and Reach. Tends to be filler alongside a playable but is quite potent. Helps you trade without an evo against awkward 8/2's that threaten board, manages trading boards to your favor and is a solid enough draw late game.

Shield Angel.FIELD7: Depends on the deck for this one. You can draft a anti early game with 1/3's 2/3's and this and have quite a good time vs early drops. Big enough late to soak damage while not dying to low drops right away and small to deter removal. Still filleresque.

Lizardman.FIELD7: Not winning you the game but the double ward evo is relavent if your getting zooed down and stablizing late and the stats + ability is solid at all parts of the game. Solid pick alongside another playable uncommon.

Goliath.FIELD7: You need some 4's especially going first if you don't go deep in 2 drops. Sometimes you don't get a lot of class specific ones or need something to drop without wasting an evo charge. This fits the bill and is solid enough.

Angelic Sword Maiden.FIELD7: Some crafts are missing a good 5 drop, This is one that can fill in the slot and gives solid enough 2 for 1's with an evolve charge. Not too great without one and a tad less impactful lategame vs strong fatties.

Unicorn Dancer Unica.FIELD7: Solid filler does a little more for lategame crafts and blood sometimes since it soaks up 2 damage either through forcing a manditory trade or her heal passive. Also would eat bread with her.

Imperial Mammoth.FIELD7: Just a vanilla fatty for the filler. Dominates many post evolve boards and gives everycraft a dragon quality fatty.

Wind God.FIELD7: Tends to be passable in any follower based draft. Big enough with an evolve and relavent buffs. Quite a bit better the closer you draft a constucted sword, shadow, blood, fairy etc agrro list.

Archangel Reina.FIELD7: Explosive effect and you blitz people out of weenies like 4 sword knights or fairies. Too much win more I feel but you will pick this every few piles she's offered and she can do some work with even just 1 evolve giving a pseudo anthem boost to team.

Fighter.FIELD7: Vanilla but gets the job done as an early drop if you need it.

Cloud Chorus.FIELD7: A bit more exciting than it's attack gain twin as it lets you save your creature in a trade acting as a "fight" sort of removal spell. Unfortunately not on a body like the Fencers and Gabriels of the game. Never pick this over onther P2 of strong spells/creatures.

Angelic Barrage.FIELD7: It tends to be a bit better a ping lategame than snipe as 3 vs 1 mana late game isn't as much and the spread obviously skews trades a lot. Hits some of the popular crafts hard and it alongside a solid curve can keep the board undercontrol.

Raging Ettin.FIELD7: 1 mana understated but a lovable ability later in the game for most crafts and fair for a neutral.

Goblin.FIELD7: Filler alongside quality card or emergancy earlygame slot late in draft. 1/2's for 1 are good enough for a low curving deck though to fight board from the start.

Angelic Snipe.FIELD7: Ping is good and flexible in Arena where you can fill in a curve and make a good trade without evolving, not better than most uncommons offered though.

Minotaur.FIELD7: A bit underwhelming early but low drop ward late helps make board awkward later. Not great with tokenmakers and pings.

Mercenary Drifter.FIELD7: Not as good as a 3/2 body but it gives you a 3 drop if your curve needs filling. Nothing fancy but will save your curve early sometimes.

Desert Rider.FIELD7: A bit worse statling than Goliath unless your drafting heavy aggro but trades into bigger stuff a bit better. Dies to a couple more removals but not a real factor to consider when drafting. About the same strength a bit to goliath in general but nice fillers to your 4 drop.

Keen Enchantment.FIELD7: Cerberus puppet barely worth the card but helps trade without an evolve at times. Mainly only good when ahead and sets u back a card when catching up with a trade.

Well of Destiny.FIELD7: It's not great but almost servicable filler. Quite win more but when it gets going like in a mirror match some trades can end up skewed. Still not worth drafting unless u get like 15 1 drops in sword.

Urd.FIELD7: You need like 8 cute things to do with this before it's consistant. A bit understated but still servicable. Reseting followers is also a good perc. Potential alongside another servicable rare/legend but she wouldn't be my drawing factor to that pile.

Harnessed Flame.FIELD7: Only pick this if your getting something godly in the pile or the other one is garbage. U can also consider it in a super aggro draft that has 15+ 1/2 drops.

Bellringer Angel.FIELD7: The card itself could just be a better uncommon unless its drafted beside something premium. On 2 it pushes you back on tempo and only helps wall board later. Replacing itself isn't as strong in lower card quality and inconsistancy of arena.

Prince of Darkness.FIELD7: Some games effectively end at turn 5 where he rots in your hand/deck. Other's in 15. Most decks want the effect late but sometimes you wish he was a fire lizard in your dragoncraft or something. Not as auto pick for me but quite tempting alongside something else good.

Angel Crusher.FIELD7: Not worth it, vanilla + a bit when put out with an empty hand but takes up a 6(kinda) slot and rots in ur hand when you might need to drop something.

Trail of Light.FIELD7: Unexciting cycle but unlike bellringer gets the card right away which a bit is more useful lategame.  Early game this is much worse to have though.

Altered Fate.FIELD7: Some cool stuff to do midgame but sets youback tempo on critical turns that you should be dropping something midrange or 2 low drops. Useless lategame and no combos to draw into in Arena. Also your other rare has to be amazing or have terrible cards in the other P2.

Path to Purgatory.FIELD7: Maybe if you get this with an altered fate in fairy P2 to make people think they in constructed. But yah no.

Demonic Simulacrum.FIELD7: Worse than Ding Dong. Super Win more and not waifu.

Fortunehunter Feena.FIELD7: One of the greatest 5 drop evos of all time, I would say this is an amazing card.

Bahamut.FIELD7: Board clear + best body in game is amazing, the question is will the game go long enough.

Gourmet Emporor Khaiza.FIELD7: Haven't drafted one yet but I have high hopes for this card, as it should generate insane card advantage. Might be too slow for TT though.

Goblin Mage.FIELD7: Maintaining tempo with instant draw, this seems pretty strong. Comparative to Thief.

Goblinbreaker Teena.FIELD7: A worse dragon warrior, 2 vs 3 is a pretty big deal. Still great filler though, especially for crafts lacking in 4s

Lucius, Goblin Slayer.FIELD7: Counters sword, the most dominant craft in TT, so this should be pretty good.

Call of Cocytus.FIELD7: I'm going to put this under DoD for now as the upside is good but slow.

Hamsa.FIELD7: This seems pretty good, should be a reliable 2/2 with big upside.

Angel of the Word.FIELD7: Comparable to Fire Lizard, the ping is worth at least 1.

Sahaquiel.FIELD7: I've drafted this and it was quite underwhelming honestly. There aren't enough neutrals for this to proc usefully, making this a 7 mana 4/4 a lot of the time.

Valkyrie's Spear.FIELD7: Significantly worse than Well of Destiny and that is a pretty bad card
